# Local env
.env

# Secret files (Part 1 of the lab). Only the *.example files and the README
# are tracked — a real secret must never be committed. If `git status` lists
# anything else under secrets/, stop and fix it before committing.
/secrets/*
!/secrets/*.example
!/secrets/README.md

# Ignition 8.3 secrets-management key files: services/config/ignition/keys/
# (root.json + kek.json) ARE deliberately committed in this lab. They are
# dummy seed keys that make the committed embedded ciphertexts decrypt on
# every student's LOCAL gateway — and on no other gateway, because
# .deployignore keeps them out of the deploy payload. In a real repo these
# files are the secret and must never be committed (see
# docs/secrets-management.md §4); committing them here is the lab's
# starting-state anti-pattern, on purpose.

# Local scratch notes used during the lab
NOTES.local.md

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editors
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# Python (used by any lab tooling)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/
.pytest_cache/


# Database files
**/db/
**/metricsdb/
**/autobackup/
**/datacache/
**/config/ignition/tags/*.idb
**/db_backup_sqlite.idb
**/valueStore.idb

# Cache and temporary files
**/jar-cache/
**/request
**/response
*.tmp
*.bak
**/var

# Log files
*.log
**/logs

# Certificates and security
**/certificates/
**/keystore/

# Runtime configuration (environment-specific)
**/config/local
**/config/resources/local

# The gateway-owned INTERNAL identity: the default user source (users.json
# holds the admin password hash!), its identity provider, and the OPC-UA
# module's user source belong to ONE gateway. Committing them ships your
# local gateway's admin credentials to every gateway you deploy to — and
# locks everyone out of test/production. Identity resources you configure yourself
# (a database or AD user source, a SAML/OIDC identity provider) hold no
# password data and ARE tracked and deployed like any other config.
**/config/resources/core/ignition/user-source/default/
**/config/resources/core/ignition/user-source/opcua-module/
**/config/resources/core/ignition/identity-provider/default/

# Test/production gateway state (bind mounts written by the gateways + CI deploys,
# see docker-compose.yaml). The README stays so the folder is visible in
# every clone.
/gateways/*
!/gateways/README.md

# Gateway-specific runtime files
**/.container-init.conf

# Backup and converted files
**/conversion-report.txt
**.digest.json

# Project conversion artifacts
**/projects/conversion-report.txt
**/migration-log-*.md
**/.resources/

# Alarm history files
**/.alarms_*

**/themes.digest.json
**/fonts.digest.json
**/icons.digest.json
